definitions:
to get into, to get in
meterse en problemas ― to get in trouble.
Está tratando de meterse en tu cabeza. ― He's trying to get into your head.

to mess with, meddle, to get involved, to involve oneself, to stick one's nose
¡No te metas en lo que no te importa! ― Don't get involved in other people's business!/ Don't meddle in others' affairs!
description: meterse (first-person singular present me meto, first-person singular preterite me metí, past participle metido)
